default2.8 
defaultOverall it showed around half of all low achievers at school are white British boys and 
defaultthat 
defaultwhite British pupils from low socio-economic status backgrounds make the least progress during secondary school.  Eligibility for free school meals has a strong link with low achievement across all pupils, but this link appears to be stronger for White Bri
defaulttish pupils than for other ethnic groups. 
defaultThis means that the attainment of White British pupils seems to be more adversely affected by socio-economic disadvantage than is the case for other ethnic groups. 
default&#xa0;
default2.9 However, t
defaulthe group with the lowest achieveme
defaultnt at secondary school are white Traveller children; 20% achieve no GCSE/GNVQ passes.
